      <scopecontent id="aspace_sc">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The New Haven Music Club Papers consist of 3 ledger books in which are entered membership lists, programs, financial records, and photographs documenting 25 years of the Club's history.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_bh1">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Music Club, a local women's club, was created in 1913 in New Haven, Conn. Meetings included concerts and recitals presented once every month by Club members. The membership of the Club consisted of Yale faculty wives and women from the New Haven community. The Music Club's last meeting was held in March, 1946.</p>  
      </bioghist>
